      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the beans are softening, add the <strong>drained chickpeas</strong> to the pan with the<strong> chopped tomato</strong>,<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>tomato paste </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant, then add a splash of <strong>cold water</strong> and cook, covered, for an initial 4-5 min or until the green beans are tender with a bite</p><p>Once tender, cook for a final 1-2 min, uncovered, or until the liquid has evaporated</p>",
